commentary: Masakadza to Younis Khan, no run Masakadza has dropped him once, and then dropped him a second time! That's one way to look at it. Another is to say that he almost pulled off magic there. Full ball on off stump, and Younis drilled it back violently at Masakadza. He did well to get his hands in position to catch it, but it did not stick, and popped up well to his right. Masakadza regrouped, dived full length to his right, but the ball landed just out of his reach. What an effort!

Masakadza regrouped, dived full length to his right, but the ball landed just out of his reach. What an effort!

commentary: Utseya to Asad Shafiq, SIX runs boy, this is a full-on acrobatics show from Zimbabwe! Kyle Jarvis does some daredevilry at the long-on fence this time. Shafiq charges out, looks to launch it over long-on, but he's not quite to the pitch. Still, he makes reasonable contact and hits it really straight. Jarvis screams across from long-on, leaps across while sticking his left hand out and nearly plucks the best catch of all-time. Nearly.

commentary: Chigumbura to Shoaib Malik, OUT Elton Chigumbura takes a blinder on the rebound! Zimbabwe's fielding continues to be a Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde show. Full ball on off stump, Malik got into the drive and hit it to the left of the bowler at shin-height. Elton reacted superbly on his follow through to pluck it low to his left as he skid and tumbled alongside it.

commentary: Jarvis to Younis Khan, OUT another stunning return catch, and Pakistan are in a spot of strife here. It was in many ways a replay of Malik's dismissal - full ball, eliciting the drive to the left of the bowler, who reacted rapidly to tumble and pluck it low, with both hands this time, on his follow through. Younis seemed to be drawn into the shot early and couldn't keep it down. 300 too optimistic now?

Younis seemed to be drawn into the shot early and couldn't keep it down. 300 too optimistic now?

commentary: Sohail Tanvir to Sibanda, 1 run another direct hit and umpire Russel Tiffin goes upstairs. Vusi is in some strife here. He advanced down the track and worked a length ball towards mid-on. Shafiq motored towards the ball, swooped, picked up and hurled the stumps down at the bowler's end. Strange running that from Vusi, he wasn't at full stretch and seemed to ground his bat at an angle away from the stumps. Very close. Might be saved by a frame. The bat was on the line by the looks of it, when the stumps broke. Saved. The third umpire took for ever, and there was some doubt. You could say Vusi was a little lucky there.

commentary: Yasir Shah to Taibu, OUT Younis Khan, take a bow! And they actually dropped this man from their team. He may be old, he may be close to the end of his career, but he's still among the fittest guys in this side. Short from Yasir, but he has the ability to skid along faster than you'd imagine. That's what spoiled Taibu's heaved sweep, but he should have still been safe. Someone forgot to tell Younis who zipped across to his right, dived full length and plucked it.

Short from Yasir, but he has the ability to skid along faster than you'd imagine. That's what spoiled Taibu's heaved sweep, but he should have still been safe. Someone forgot to tell Younis who zipped across to his right, dived full length and plucked it.
